Materials and Tools Required:
Paper, pens and post-it notes;
Recording equipment, such as a camera or a smartphone;
Audio recorder (optional);
Miro (or similar online whiteboard tool);
Video editing software (for example, Adobe Premiere Pro, iMovie);
Instagram or Social Media account;
Wi-Fi access and basic digital literacy.

Materials Needed:
Character development worksheets;
Art supplies for drawing or visualisation (optional);
Audio/video clips or species profiles (optional);
Comfortable space for group dialogue.
Optional: Digital tools for remote or online sessions (such as video conferencing software, digital workspace access and shared online documents)

Materials and Conditions Required:
A quiet, safe, and comfortable space for seated or floor-based meditation
Optional: cushions, chairs, or blankets for comfort;
Printed or digital Earth Crisis System Diagrams (from Bridget McKenzie's frameworks);
Character or species prompt cards (optional);
Paper, a shared board or screen (for sharing discussion points);
A facilitator with experience in somatic or meditative guidance;
Optional: small props or natural objects (feathers, leaves, bones, shells).
In addition, the following could be integrated:
Use visual aids: species photos, maps, soundscapes;
Record the sharing circle (with permission) for artistic/archival use;
Create collective artwork, word clouds, or visual diaries post-session;
Consider co-facilitation with a young person or neurodiverse co-leader.
